 via GIPHY  English: Hello, can you speak English? IsiZulu: Sawubona, uyakwazi ukukhuluma isiNgisi? IsiXhosa: Molo, uyakwazi ukuthetha isiNgesi? Afrikaans: Hallo, kan jy Engels praat? Sepedi: Thobela, na obelelu Seisimane? SeTswana: Dumela, * bua Seisimane? SeSotho: Dumela, * bua Seisimane? XiTsonga: Avuxeni, Xana wa xitiva Xinghezi ke? SiSwati: Sawubona, uyasati yini siNgisi? TshiVenda: Ndaa (male) Aa (female) Vha a amba English naa? Ndebele: Sawubona, ukhuluma isiNgisi?   2. Pleasantries      English: How are you? IsiZulu: Unjani? IsiXhosa: Unjani? Afrikaans: Hoe gaan dit? Sepedi: O kae? SeTswana: O tsogile jang? SeSotho: U phela joang? XiTsonga: Kunjhani? SiSwati: Unjani? TshiVenda: Vho vuwa hani? Ndebele: Linjani?  3. Gratitude      English: Thank you, man! IsiZulu: Ngiyabonga mphitshi yami IsiXhosa: Enkosi mchana Afrikaans: Dankie, man! Sepedi: Ke a leboga SeTswana: Ke a leboga / Ke itumtese SeSotho: Kea leboha, monna! XiTsonga: Ndzi khense ngopfu SiSwati: Ngiyabonga TshiVenda: Ndi a livhuwa Ndebele: Ndi a livhuwa  4. Loo matters     English: Where’s the toilet/bathroom? IsiZulu: Ikuphi indlu encane? IsiXhosa: Iphi indlu yangasese? Afrikaans: Waar is die badkamer? Sepedi: Na Ntlwana Ya Boithomelo E Kae? SeTswana: Ntlwanaboithusetso E Fa Kae? SeSotho: Ntlwana E Ho Kae? XiTsonga: Xana Xihambukelo Xi Le Kwihi? SiSwati: Uphi Umthoyi? TshiVenda: U Bunga Li Ngafhi? Ndebele: Ikhuphi Indlwana Yokuzithumela Itoyilede?  5. Feelings English: I love you. IsiZulu / Ndebele: Ngiyakuthanda IsiXhosa: Ndiyakuthanda Afrikaans: Ek is lief vir jou Sepedi / SeSotho: Kea u rata SeTswana: Ke a go rata XiTsonga: Ndza ku rhandza SiSwati: Ngiyakutsandza TshiVenda: Ndi a ni funa 6. Pardon     English: Excuse me IsiZulu / IsiXhosa: Uxolo Afrikaans: Verskoon my Sepedi: Ntshwarele SeTswana: Nxae SeSotho: Tshwarelo XiTsonga: Ndzi khomeli SiSwati: Lucolo TshiVenda: Kha vha mpfarele Ndebele: Ngitshidele  7. Apologies      English: I am sorry IsiZulu: Ngiyaxolisa IsiXhosa: Ndicela uxolo Afrikaans: Ek is jammer Sepedi / SeTswana: Ke maswabi SeSotho: Ntshwarele XiTsonga: Ndzi kombela ku khomeriwa TshiVenda: Ndi khou humbela pfarelo Ndebele / SiSwati: Ngiyacolisa 8. Travelling      English: Have a safe journey IsiZulu: Ube nohambo oluhle IsiXhosa: Hamba kakuhle Afrikaans: Veilige reis Sepedi: O be le leeto le le bolokegilego SeTswana: Nna le mosepele o o babalesegileng! SeSotho: O tsamaye hantle XiTsonga: Famba hi ku rhula SiSwati: Ube (singular) / Nibe (plural) neluhambo loluphephile TshiVenda: Vha vhe na lwendo lwavhudi Ndebele: Ube nekhambo eliphephileko 9. Assistance      English: Help! IsiZulu: Siza! IsiXhosa: Nceda! Afrikaans: Hulp! Sepedi / SeTswana / SeSotho: Thusang! XiTsonga: Ndzi pfuneni! SiSwati: Sita (singular) / sitani (plural)! TshiVenda: Thuso! Ndebele: Ndzi pfuneni!  Follow on Twitter: @IOSNewsSA  Independent On Saturday